<font color="#FF0000">THANKS FLOYD AND REGINA!</font><br>
<tt>Thu Dec 18 19:33:51 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Regina:<br><br>
We are a shot up, crippled, old, near sighted, over weight, hard of hearing, traumatized bunch of fellows who, in spite of our physical limitations would stand in the gap for you and yours tomorrow if necessary.  Fortunately for you and for us..other young men and women are prepared to go in our place.<br>
If Floyd were alive he would be standing in our midst, arguing, agreeing, participating in our dumb humor and very much be a part of us!  In our hearts and yours he is still alive as are all my friends and my little brother who perished in our behalf.<br>
As long as any man or woman will stand up against tyrany there courage is fueled by the likes of Floyd and all those before and after him who made the supreme sacrifice for others.<br><br>
God Bless You and your family, Happy Holidays, and Thank You for your powerful statement above!  Floyd would probably want all of us to enjoy the freedom that he bought for us!<br><br>
Captain Edward Ramon U.S. Army RVN '66'67'69
